  "prompt": "What is the procedure of getting admission into IIT for NRIs?",
  "response": "For NRIs (Non-Resident Indians) seeking admission to IITs, the primary procedure involves:\n\n1. Eligibility Criteria:\n- 10+2 or equivalent examination with Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics\n- Minimum 75% marks in 12th standard\n- Age limit: Usually below 25 years\n\n2. Admission Routes:\na) JEE Advanced (Main pathway)\n- Appear for JEE Main\n- Qualify for JEE Advanced\n- Participate in JEE Advanced counseling\n\nb) Direct Admission of Students Abroad (DASA)\n- Specifically designed for NRIs and Overseas Citizens of India (OCI)\n- Separate application process\n- Different eligibility criteria\n- Seat allocation through online counseling\n\n3. Required Documents:\n- Passport\n- Mark sheets\n- Birth certificate\n- Academic transcripts\n- Proof of NRI/OCI status\n- Recommendation letters\n- Valid entrance exam scores\n\n4. Application Process:\n- Online registration\n- Submit required documents\n- Pay application fees\n- Appear for entrance exams\n- Participate in counseling\n\n5. Reservation:\n- Some seats reserved specifically for NRI candidates\n\nCandidates should check specific IIT websites for updated and precise admission guidelines.",
